HEADWORD: Billy
<hw>Bil"ly</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A club;
esp., a policeman's club. Also called <altname>billy
club</altname></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Wool Manuf.)</fld> <def>A slubbing or roving
machine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Billy club</ent>⟦br⟧
